  Spanish coins from E up to I.

      @{"  Escudo  " link escu}   @{"  Ecu " link ecu}   @{"  Euro  " link euro}   @{"  Florin  " link flor}

@endnode
@node escu " ESCUDO-SHIELD"

   Coin  ancient of  gold,  68 were  entering a  mark the  same as the
crowns.

   Coin of silver that was worth 10 royal of @{"fleece" link diccio}.

@endnode
@node ecu " ECU"

   Imaginary  coin that  preceded the Euro,  used only in  processings
Bank.

@endnode
@node Euro " EURO"

   Coin of the European Union, it's official traffic  began on January
1 of 2002.

@endnode
@node flor " FLORIN"

   Coin of  gold ordered  mint for  the kings  of Aragon,  copying the
Florins or Florencia's duchies; its value suffered greats  alterations
for effect of the abuse of @{"liga" link diccio} in the metal.

@endnode

@node colo3 " M-J"

  Spanish coins from M up to J.

      @{"  Kirate  " link kira}   @{"  Libra  " link lira}     @{"  Mancuso  " link man}   @{"  Maravedi  " link mara}

