@node kira " KIRATE"

   Coin ancient of Al-Andalus  that ordered  to mint Ali ben Yusuf, it
was of silver and copper.

@endnode
@node lira " LIBRA-POUND"

   Catalan pound: Imaginary  coin that  was divided  in 20 salaries or
240 dineros  and it was  equivalent to  two pesetas and  seventy seven
cents.

   Aragon pound or jaquesa: Imaginary coin of  equal division that the
Catalan pound but with value of 4 pesetas and 71 cents.

   Majorcan pound: Imaginary coin  of equal division  that the Catalan
pound but with value of 3 pesetas and 32 cents.

   Navarre pound: Imaginary coin that  was equivalent  to 78 cents and
was divided in the same salaries and dineros that the Catalan pound.

   Valencian pound: Imaginary coin of equal  division that the Catalan
pound but with value of 3 pesetas and 75 cents.

@endnode
@node man " MANCUSO"

   Coin ancient of gold ordered mint for Ramon Berenguer I.

@endnode
@node mara " MARAVEDI"

   Also named maravedis, maravedises and maravedies.

   Maravedi Alfonsi or white: Maraveri of silver.

   Maravedi of Burgos: Coin of @{"fleece" link diccio} with  three parts  of copper and
one of  silver worked in Burgos for Alfonso X, who was worth the sixth
part of the maravedi of silver.

   Maravedi of copper: Coin ancient that was worth two blancas.

   Maravedi of gold: Golden  coin of 16  carats of  Alfonso X, who was
equivalent to 6 maravedis of silver.

   Maravedi of silver: Coin previous to the Catolic Kings, whose value
it was  the third  part of the one royal ancient silver or 20 cents of
peseta approximately.

   Maravedi noven: Old maravedi.

   New Maravedi: Coin  ancient of  @{"fleece" link diccio} that  was equivalent  to the
seventh one part of the royal one of silver.

   Compressed Maravedi: Coin ancient of minor value that the blanca.

   Old Maravedi: Coin  of  @{"fleece" link diccio}  that  circulated  in  Castile  from
Fernando IV up to the Catolic Kings,  that it was worth the third part
of the royal one of silver.

@endnode
@node mea " MEAJA"

   Coin of @{"fleece" link diccio} that circulated ancient in Castile and it was worth
the sixth one part of a dinero or half maravedi of Burgos.

@endnode
@node meti " METICAL"

   Coin of @{"fleece" link diccio} that circulated in Spain in the century XIII.

@endnode
@node mora " MORABETIN/O"

   Coin @{"almoravide" link diccio} of silver, very small.

@endnode

