@node ocha " OCHAVO"

   Coin of copper with weight of the eighth one of  ounce and value of
two maravedis,  coined by Philip III  until the middle  of the century
XIX, but diminished its weigh even that preserving the original value.

@endnode
@node onz " ONZA-OUNCE"

   Golden coin coined from Philip III up to Fernando VII and value 320
royals or 80 pesetas.

@endnode
@node pepi " PEPION"

   Tiny coin used in Castile in the century XIII and whose value fixed
Alfonso X in 18 divides from a metical.

@endnode
@node pese " PESETA"

   Born coin on October 19, 1868 for decree: the peseta of silver with
5 grs  of  weight,  of  law  0,835  thousandth,  alloy  of  copper and
tolerances  of 0,002 on  law  and 0,003  on weight,  the law of  20 of
january of 1939,  it deprived of legal tender  the currency of silver,
and on March 1, 2002 disappear definitively by the arrive of Euro.

@endnode
@node peta " PESETA COLUMNARIA"

   The coined  in America,  which has the  shield of the  royal weapon
between columns and value five royal of fleece.

@endnode
@node peso " PESO"

   Unit monetary of diverse countries of America and The Philippines.

   There was coined weight that circulated simultaneously that it own
coins  into Spain,  in the  colonies like Cuba,  Puerto Rico  and The
Philippines.

@endnode

